# STATE MANAGEMENT RULES

> Right state in the right place. Not everything needs a global store.

---

## STATE TYPES

```
Server state → fetch / SWR / React Query
Client state → Context / useState / Zustand
Form state   → React Hook Form + Zod
URL state    → useSearchParams / nuqs
```

---

## DECISION TREE

```
Data from server?
├── Yes → fetch in component / Server Component
└── No
    └── Needs to be in URL?
        ├── Yes → useSearchParams
        └── No
            └── Global?
                ├── Yes → Context (useCart, useSettings)
                └── No
                    └── Form data?
                        ├── Yes → React Hook Form
                        └── No → useState
```

---

## CURRENT PROJECT PATTERNS

- **Cart:** Context + localStorage (`useCart`)
- **Settings:** Context (`useSettings`)
- **Auth:** NextAuth SessionProvider
- **Forms:** React Hook Form + Zod

---

## ANTI-PATTERNS

```tsx
// ❌ Duplicating state
const [localUser, setLocalUser] = useState(user);

// ❌ Derived state in useState
const [total, setTotal] = useState(0);
useEffect(() => setTotal(items.reduce(...)), [items]);

// ✅ Derive directly
const total = items.reduce((sum, i) => sum + i.price, 0);
```

